# Development Guidelines

## Environment Compatibility
- Ensure code works in both local and HPC environments
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Support both CPU and GPU operations

## Data Integrity
- Implement data validation checks
- Use checksums for data verification
- Maintain data lineage
- Document data transformations

## Scientific Computing
- Follow scientific computing best practices
- Use appropriate numerical precision
- Implement proper error propagation
- Document assumptions and limitations

## Error Handling
- Implement robust error handling
- Log errors appropriately
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Handle edge cases gracefully

## Documentation
- Document all data processing steps
- Include code comments for complex logic
- Maintain up-to-date README files
- Document environment setup
